{"word":"ἀπόφημι","slug":"ἀπόφημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπόφημι</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to speak out, declare flatly</i> or <i>plainly</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to say no</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to refuse, deny</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}